AKS Architecture
1: Azure AKS CLUSTER CONTROL PLAINE
  A: Container Runtinme(docker)
  B: kube-schedular-> It is responsible for distributing containers on worker nodes. it watches newly created pods which are not assigned to any 
     nodes .it assignsthe nodes to run on them.
  C: etcd: it is the backend of kubernetes that stores all master and waorker node related inf in key value pairs.
  D: kube-api-server: it is frontend of k8's . it exposes k8's to external world
  E: kube-controller-manaer: It watches everything containers, pods, nodes on worker node. There are different type of controllers that manages 
     everything.
